        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>synthetic inorganic black pigment [300013175], black pigment [300013135], pigment by color [300013134], pigments [300013109], colorant (material) [300013026], materials by function [300014692], materials (substances) [300010358], Materials (hierarchy name) [300010357], Materials Facet [300264091]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Synthetically prepared black iron oxide pigment that is permanent, having a warm brownish black color, existing as a dense, heavy powder, and unlike most naturally produced black iron oxide pigments, it is magnetic. Mars black was developed in the early 20th century; it is used in oil paints, watercolors, and mortars and cements, because it does not effloresce.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種合成調製而成的氧化鐵黑色顏料，永久不褪色，色澤呈暖棕黑，以高密度、質重的粉末狀態存在。其具有磁性，不同於大部分天然製造的氧化鐵黑色顏料。馬爾斯黑發展於二十世紀初期，因為不會風化，所以用於油畫、水彩、灰漿及水泥。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
